result.execSummary:
The defendant Carly J Musha was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Carly J Musha in court with attorney Jonathan A. Lavoy.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

AS TO COUNT 1:

On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 450.11(7)(a), a class U Misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Court sentenced defendant to serve ONE (1) DAY in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for ONE (1) day served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2.

AS TO COUNT 2:

On motion of the state, court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.  

Court sentenced defendant to serve ONE (1) DAY in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for ONE (1) day served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1.

AS TO COUNT 3:

On motion of the state, court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to Possess Drug Paraphernalia, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.573(1).

Court sentenced defendant to serve ONE (1) DAY in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for ONE (1) day served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1, 2.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 11-15-2017 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
